# Piper TTS voice models live here.
#
# Run `bash Tools/download_voice_models.sh` to populate this folder with
# .onnx weights + .onnx.json configs for the canonical voice casting
# (see Docs/VOICE_CASTING.md). The .onnx / .onnx.json files themselves
# are NOT committed to git — they are large (50–70 MB each) and trivially
# re-downloadable from https://huggingface.co/rhasspy/piper-voices.
#
# Per D-059, the script + casting table + this directory are the source
# of truth; the model files are user-generated artifacts.
